WEBVTT

00:05.939 --> 00:09.241
(GHOSTLY VOCALIZING)

00:15.382 --> 00:17.950
(RAP BEAT PLAYING)

00:20.053 --> 00:22.021
(HARD ROCK PLAYING)

00:22.023 --> 00:23.422
(SCREAMING)

00:35.168 --> 00:37.536
(BATS SQUEAKING)

00:42.575 --> 00:45.144
Wow, slow day huh?

00:45.146 --> 00:48.280
(CRASHING)

00:51.017 --> 00:54.920
Seems like we need to
drum up more business, hmm?

00:54.922 --> 01:00.459
Let me guess.
You have another
fang-tastic idea.

01:00.461 --> 01:02.528
Well since you asked.

01:02.530 --> 01:04.596
Parties.
(CLUCKING)

01:04.964 --> 01:07.766
We make Hotel Transylvania
the go-to place

01:07.768 --> 01:10.002
for after-funerals,
anniver-scaries.

01:10.004 --> 01:12.771
We create buzz...
(FLIES BUZZING)

01:12.773 --> 01:15.274
The good kind,
not the swarm-of-locusts kind.

01:15.276 --> 01:17.743
Absolutely not.
I detest parties.

01:17.745 --> 01:19.311
Come on,
how about this?

01:19.313 --> 01:21.346
Let me throw
a sample party,

01:21.348 --> 01:23.415
to prove
I can do it. Huh?

01:23.417 --> 01:25.984
(SIGHS) It would
have to be simple.

01:25.986 --> 01:28.854
A group of monsters
sitting around,
waiting for death,

01:28.856 --> 01:29.888
you know, a party.

01:29.890 --> 01:32.424
Of course, entertainment,
maybe a cake,

01:32.426 --> 01:34.226
definitely a cake.
But that's it.

01:34.228 --> 01:36.395
And someone's birthday
is coming up,

01:36.397 --> 01:40.799
someone who's
totally unimportant
in every conceivable way.

01:40.801 --> 01:41.967
Diane?

01:41.969 --> 01:42.835
(CLUCKING)

01:42.837 --> 01:45.003
It would
get her off my back.

01:45.005 --> 01:46.205
But entertainment?

01:46.207 --> 01:49.541
I've found classy options
for every occasion,

01:49.543 --> 01:50.676
even the boring ones.

01:50.678 --> 01:51.844
AUNT LYDIA:
Octavio the Awesome?

01:51.846 --> 01:54.546
Is he still doing
the tedious
old magic act?

01:54.548 --> 01:57.216
Yes! And he's
totally available,

01:57.218 --> 01:58.350
surprisingly so.

01:58.352 --> 01:59.051
I did my research.

01:59.053 --> 02:02.354
Well then,
throw your test party,
with Octavio.

02:02.356 --> 02:06.225
If you fail, you can scrape
the fungus off Bigfoot's toes

02:06.227 --> 02:07.759
for the next year.

02:07.761 --> 02:09.127
(RETCHING)

02:10.797 --> 02:12.197
(GRUNTING)

02:12.199 --> 02:15.367
How do you do always come up
with the worst punishment?

02:15.369 --> 02:15.901
It's a gift.

02:15.903 --> 02:18.971
But it's not one of
your disgusting
party gifts.

02:18.973 --> 02:23.008
Right this way,
front row seats for
the Beak of Honor.

02:23.010 --> 02:25.944
(CLUCKING) So excited!

02:25.946 --> 02:28.213
(CHATTERING)

02:28.215 --> 02:29.915
Festive decorations, Mavis.

02:29.917 --> 02:33.352
Yeah, they really make me
look forward to my funeral.

02:33.354 --> 02:36.588
Exactly!
Enjoy the show!

02:36.590 --> 02:38.023
I highly doubt it.

02:38.025 --> 02:40.225
(APPLAUSE)
(LAUGHS) Thank you!

02:40.227 --> 02:41.727
I'm your host, Pedro.

02:41.729 --> 02:45.764
And this is Diane:
A Night of Celebration.

02:45.766 --> 02:49.134
How's everyone doing?
Anyone here from the grave?

02:49.136 --> 02:50.869
(GROWLING)

02:52.138 --> 02:53.472
The warm-up acts
are ready to go.

02:53.474 --> 02:57.042
And Octavio the Awesome
should arrive
any second now.

02:57.044 --> 03:00.913
It's going so well.
I can practically
taste the cake.

03:00.915 --> 03:04.550
Quasi's whipping
the scream cheese frosting
as we speak.

03:04.784 --> 03:06.885
(SCREAMING)

03:06.887 --> 03:08.687
Looks at him.
And he says

03:08.689 --> 03:12.991
"Sir, that's no sarcophagus.
That's the toilet!"

03:13.726 --> 03:14.927
(ALL LAUGHING)

03:14.929 --> 03:18.030
Wonderful!

03:18.498 --> 03:19.831
(TICKING)

03:19.833 --> 03:21.500
Being a doctor is tough.

03:21.502 --> 03:24.369
Last week, patient comes in
with a cough.

03:24.371 --> 03:25.370
So, I run some tests.

03:25.372 --> 03:27.839
Now I've got to schlep
all the way to his swamp

03:27.841 --> 03:30.676
to tell him he's got
six months to live.

03:30.678 --> 03:32.911
There go my dinner plans!

03:34.480 --> 03:35.747
(GARY COUGHING)

03:35.749 --> 03:38.784
Gary? I was just
talking about you!

03:38.786 --> 03:41.253
What? I have six months
to live?

03:41.255 --> 03:44.122
Nah, I didn't want my act
to be a downer.

03:44.124 --> 03:46.525
You have two months
to live!

03:47.227 --> 03:50.562
(ALL LAUGHING)

03:50.564 --> 03:53.799
(LAUGHING CONTINUES)

03:53.801 --> 03:55.067
Is there anything funnier

03:55.069 --> 03:57.269
than a monster's
impending doom?

03:57.271 --> 03:59.571
Aww, look at Aunt Lydia.

03:59.573 --> 04:02.374
We are going to host
so many parties.

04:02.376 --> 04:06.578
I think someone's in line
for a promotion.

04:06.580 --> 04:08.647
That's my time!
Good night!

04:08.649 --> 04:11.416
And good luck, Gary.
(APPLAUSE)

04:11.418 --> 04:15.721
Wait a sec.
Where's that Octavio?
If he doesn't show...

04:15.723 --> 04:19.791
Mavis! Octavio
the Awesomely Late
is here!

04:19.793 --> 04:22.494
Yes! Better late
than severed!

04:25.965 --> 04:29.101
Octavio, welcome!
At last!
(GASPS)

04:29.103 --> 04:32.271
Sorry, I had trouble
with the map.

04:32.605 --> 04:33.672
Well you're here now.

04:33.674 --> 04:37.175
And everyone is so,
so eager to see
your act!

04:37.177 --> 04:41.713
Great! I'll open with the old
ear-behind-the-ear trick.

04:45.018 --> 04:48.820
Whoops! Sorry, I get clumsy
when I'm nervous.

04:48.822 --> 04:50.155
And I'm always nervous.

04:50.157 --> 04:51.023
And I'm starting to get

04:51.025 --> 04:54.259
why my Aunt Lydia
insisted I book you.

04:54.261 --> 04:55.961
Thanks, Lydia.

04:55.963 --> 04:57.296
Lydia Dracula?

04:57.298 --> 04:58.563
Oh, she hated my act
so much,

04:58.565 --> 05:01.533
she wrote a blood letter
to <i>Entertainment Shriekly.</i>

05:01.535 --> 05:03.869
"Octavio the Awful",
she said.

05:03.871 --> 05:07.973
I can't go in there.
I won't! You can't make me!

05:07.975 --> 05:09.308
Wait! No!

05:09.310 --> 05:13.178
Now what? I told everyone
we'd have a magician.

05:13.180 --> 05:16.948
And maybe we still do.

05:16.950 --> 05:19.484
Time for some magic wagic!

05:19.486 --> 05:21.720
Uh, forget I said that.

05:22.622 --> 05:25.557
<i>Magic for Beginners,</i>
<i>chapter one.</i>

05:25.559 --> 05:26.892
Show time!
(GASPS)

05:26.894 --> 05:28.293
Good luck, Mavis!

05:28.295 --> 05:29.528
(CHUCKLING) Okay,

05:29.530 --> 05:33.265
is this
a great party or what?
Whoo-hoo!

05:33.267 --> 05:34.633
(GRUNTING)

05:34.635 --> 05:35.901
Where is Octavio the Awesome?

05:35.903 --> 05:38.403
Uh, a magician never reveals
his secrets.

05:38.405 --> 05:43.208
Maybe he's already here.
Can you feel it in the air?

05:43.210 --> 05:44.976
You mean
your impending failure?

05:44.978 --> 05:49.014
No, I'm talking about
magic time!

05:49.016 --> 05:50.549
(FINGERS TAPPING)

05:50.551 --> 05:53.285
(GULPS) Oh, it's hot
up here.

05:53.287 --> 05:55.587
I'll just, uh...

05:57.156 --> 05:59.124
(BARKING)

05:59.126 --> 06:01.727
Oh, uh, ta-da!

06:01.729 --> 06:03.495
(SCREAMING)

06:03.497 --> 06:04.930
(CHEERING)

06:04.932 --> 06:06.098
Thank you. Thank you.

06:06.100 --> 06:09.434
For my next trick,
I need a volunteer.

06:09.436 --> 06:10.836
(CLUCKING) Me!

06:10.838 --> 06:13.672
All right,
let's hear it for Diane!

06:13.674 --> 06:15.574
(ALL CHEERING)

06:15.576 --> 06:20.645
I am going to make
our Beak of Honor disappear!

06:20.647 --> 06:21.980
(ALL EXCLAIM)

06:21.982 --> 06:23.215
(CLUCKING)

06:23.217 --> 06:27.519
Okay, slippity sloppy,
hoppity hey,

06:27.521 --> 06:31.189
disappear now! Go away!

06:32.325 --> 06:35.894
(LAUGHING)
Mildly impressive.

06:36.295 --> 06:36.995
It worked.

06:36.997 --> 06:41.133
Uh... I mean,
now to make her reappear.

06:41.135 --> 06:43.769
Swirly, curly,
the other way,

06:43.771 --> 06:47.406
return to us
right now. Okay?

06:47.408 --> 06:48.507
(MAVIS CLEARING THROAT)

06:48.509 --> 06:54.579
Nosfarutu, nosferack,
come on home now!
Hurry back!

06:55.114 --> 06:55.981
Holy rabies.

06:55.983 --> 06:59.918
And now
for a totally planned
magician's intermission.

06:59.920 --> 07:03.922
In my absence,
please enjoy Hank
and his famous impressions!

07:03.924 --> 07:05.924
(APPLAUSE)
(CLEARING THROAT)

07:05.926 --> 07:07.826
Velcome to my hotel!

07:07.828 --> 07:11.563
It's Dracula!
He's doing
my dopey brother!

07:11.565 --> 07:13.231
Blah, blah, blah!

07:13.233 --> 07:15.300
(LAUGHING)

07:15.401 --> 07:17.335
I made Diane disappear!

07:17.337 --> 07:19.571
We know. Awesome!

07:19.573 --> 07:21.973
No, I really
made her disappear!

07:21.975 --> 07:24.176
I have to get her back
before Quasi brings out
the cake

07:24.178 --> 07:26.745
or I'm going to be
waist-deep in fungal
toe jam!

07:26.747 --> 07:28.747
It won't come off!

07:28.749 --> 07:30.148
(RETCHING)

07:30.150 --> 07:31.716
Ew.
Yum.

07:31.718 --> 07:33.351
What did you do exactly?

07:33.353 --> 07:36.254
I just waved the wand,
like this.

07:36.256 --> 07:39.124
No! Where'd they all go?

07:40.660 --> 07:42.327
Hello?

07:42.329 --> 07:45.430
(SING-SONG) Hello?

07:45.598 --> 07:47.065
What is this place?

07:47.067 --> 07:47.799
It's not so bad,

07:47.801 --> 07:49.434
once you get used
to all the running.

07:49.436 --> 07:50.302
Sorry, "Running"?

07:50.304 --> 07:52.137
(LOUD THUMPING)
(DIANE CLUCKING)

07:52.139 --> 07:54.272
(CLUCKING)
WENDY: Ah!

07:54.274 --> 07:57.142
(DIANE CLUCKING)
(BOTH SCREAMING)

07:58.444 --> 08:01.012
Oh, my gosh, you guys,
holy rabies!

08:01.014 --> 08:05.083
(LAUGHING)
That is Mavis to a "T"!

08:05.085 --> 08:07.018
And then there's Lydia...

08:07.020 --> 08:07.619
(GROWLS)

08:07.621 --> 08:10.121
Uh, who is super terrifying
and scary.

08:10.123 --> 08:11.122
And let's leave it at that.

08:11.124 --> 08:13.391
That's pretty on point,
actually.

08:13.393 --> 08:15.494
(GROANING)
(GROWLING)

08:15.496 --> 08:18.230
Quasi is nearly finished
the cake? (GROANS)

08:18.232 --> 08:20.065
First time I've ever
dreaded dessert!

08:20.067 --> 08:22.601
I got to find Octavio.
But how?

08:22.603 --> 08:27.772
Take me to your owner!
Go to your magician!

08:27.774 --> 08:30.509
Returnio Octavio?

08:31.177 --> 08:33.211
Ah!

08:33.813 --> 08:36.381
(SOBBING)

08:36.383 --> 08:38.216
(GRUNTING)

08:38.217 --> 08:41.052
Octavio, thank darkness!
I need your help!

08:41.054 --> 08:44.756
Your wand
made my friends disappear,
and Diane!

08:44.758 --> 08:47.192
Help you?
You took my wand!

08:47.194 --> 08:48.660
You dropped it!

08:48.662 --> 08:50.328
I need my wand back!

08:50.330 --> 08:52.597
I need my friends back,
and Diane!

08:52.599 --> 08:55.400
You want your wand?
Come and get it!
Whoa!

08:55.402 --> 08:57.168
(BOTH GRUNTING)

09:00.273 --> 09:01.940
Where am I?

09:01.942 --> 09:04.376
Wendy? Pedro?

09:04.378 --> 09:06.745
BOTH: Mavis! Run!

09:06.747 --> 09:08.513
(CLUCKING)

09:08.515 --> 09:09.614
(GASPS)

09:09.616 --> 09:11.249
(CLUCKING)

09:11.251 --> 09:13.518
(GRUNTING)

09:13.520 --> 09:16.321
Give me back my wand!

09:16.323 --> 09:17.856
First, tell me
how we get out!

09:17.858 --> 09:20.759
Fine, just reverse
the swirl!

09:20.761 --> 09:21.826
I tried that!

09:21.828 --> 09:26.565
(STAMMERS) What?
But it's the only fix I know!

09:26.567 --> 09:30.268
Oh, your aunt's right.
I'm awful.

09:30.270 --> 09:31.536
(SOBBING)

09:31.538 --> 09:33.405
No, come on, don't.

09:33.407 --> 09:36.241
I just hope she hasn't
caught on yet.

09:36.243 --> 09:38.510
(ALL LAUGHING)

09:38.512 --> 09:40.645
We're dying over here!

09:40.647 --> 09:44.549
MAVIS: There's got to be
a false bottom
in this cauldron.

09:44.551 --> 09:46.217
The false bottom
would work,

09:46.219 --> 09:48.286
except you moved
the cauldron.

09:48.288 --> 09:49.454
That locks it up!

09:49.456 --> 09:52.257
(GASPS) But how do we
move it back?

09:52.692 --> 09:54.492
(GRUNTING)

09:54.494 --> 09:56.294
MAVIS: Run!

09:56.296 --> 10:01.600
(ALL SCREAMING)

10:07.940 --> 10:09.774
(DIANE CLUCKING)

10:09.776 --> 10:13.912
Wendy's Dad, Mr. Blob,
explaining the Big Bang.

10:13.914 --> 10:16.147
(BABBLING)

10:16.149 --> 10:18.216
(IMITATES EXPLOSION)

10:18.218 --> 10:20.518
(LAUGHING)

10:20.520 --> 10:21.453
Stop! Stop!

10:21.455 --> 10:24.389
My mouth isn't used
to this upturned shape!

10:24.391 --> 10:28.093
(LAUGHING)
Bring back Diane already.

10:28.095 --> 10:31.229
(ALL GRUNTING)

10:31.831 --> 10:33.365
(GROANS)

10:36.602 --> 10:37.769
Ta-da!

10:37.771 --> 10:39.137
(LAUGHING)

10:39.139 --> 10:41.673
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

10:41.675 --> 10:43.074
(CHEERING)

10:43.076 --> 10:45.543
(SING-SONG)
Just like I planned it!

10:45.545 --> 10:48.647
Oh, Diane,
I was so worried...

10:48.649 --> 10:49.314
(CLUCKING)

10:49.316 --> 10:51.483
Is what someone who cared
might say.

10:51.485 --> 10:53.518
(CLUCKING)

10:53.520 --> 10:58.723
Mavis, I must admit
you even made that hack
look good.

10:58.725 --> 11:00.358
Aw, thank you!

11:00.360 --> 11:04.062
You... You think I'm a hack?

11:04.064 --> 11:04.996
Whoo-hoo!

11:04.998 --> 11:08.199
I want a new magic show
every week!

11:08.201 --> 11:10.368
Yeah-ha-ha!

11:14.273 --> 11:15.440
(CLUCKING)

11:15.442 --> 11:17.842
(ALL SCREAMING)
You're killing me!

11:17.844 --> 11:20.211
(LAUGHING)

11:20.613 --> 11:22.981
(BATS SQUEAKING)

11:23.215 --> 11:24.783
(WOLF HOWLING)

11:24.785 --> 11:27.352
Beating artichoke hearts,
yes...

11:27.354 --> 11:28.787
(HEARTS BEATING)

11:28.789 --> 11:30.088
Gargoyled eggs...

11:30.090 --> 11:31.022
(EGGS SQUEALING)

11:31.024 --> 11:32.757
Chocolate-covered eyeballs.

11:32.759 --> 11:36.428
HANK: I got eyeballs
on the chocolate-covered
eyeballs.

11:36.430 --> 11:37.862
(GRUNTING)

11:37.864 --> 11:39.064
(GASPING)

11:39.066 --> 11:42.600
What is this?

11:42.602 --> 11:44.269
Garlic seeds?

11:44.271 --> 11:45.070
(GASPING)

11:45.072 --> 11:47.038
How could you
mess this up again?

11:47.040 --> 11:53.111
If we're caught,
Lydia will skin us alive,
and then dead!

11:53.113 --> 11:53.778
(GROWLING)

11:53.780 --> 11:56.247
Oh, sure, no big deal
for you, but for me, it's...

11:56.249 --> 12:01.086
AUNT LYDIA: Quasimodo,
where is my breakfast?

12:01.088 --> 12:01.953
(SHRIEKS)

12:01.955 --> 12:05.423
Okay, you wait for me
in the spice torture rack.

12:07.426 --> 12:09.160
<i>Saperlipopette!</i>

12:09.162 --> 12:11.930
Did he say "Garlic seeds"?

12:11.932 --> 12:15.133
The garlic patch said
"Come play with us."

12:15.135 --> 12:17.235
And the little vampire
was tempted.

12:17.237 --> 12:19.237
She disobeyed
the shrunken heads,

12:19.239 --> 12:21.740
who said
"Girl, don't go there."

12:21.742 --> 12:23.341
She even ignored
her papa,

12:23.343 --> 12:25.376
who said
"Under no circumstances,

12:25.378 --> 12:29.481
are you to look at,
touch or think
about garlic."

12:29.483 --> 12:31.282
(GASPS)
I said don't touch!

12:31.284 --> 12:33.318
What happened next
to the vampire?

12:33.320 --> 12:38.089
Next? Um, terrible, horrible,
oh, unspeakable things.

12:38.091 --> 12:40.792
I can't even talk about them,
they're so bad.

12:40.794 --> 12:45.864
Now, scary dreams,
my little pus dumpling!

12:45.866 --> 12:49.601
Wow. I've never even
seen garlic before.

12:49.603 --> 12:51.202
I got to get a closer look!

12:51.204 --> 12:52.103
No!
Stop!

12:52.105 --> 12:53.471
Mavis!
You can't go near garlic!

12:53.473 --> 12:57.776
So they say.
But what really happens?

12:57.778 --> 12:59.244
I bet it's all a myth,

12:59.246 --> 13:01.880
perpetuated by
the garlic farmers.

13:01.882 --> 13:03.848
You know how those weirdos
can be.

13:03.850 --> 13:04.783
Nope.
Not really.

13:04.785 --> 13:06.718
That's literally
just your thing, dude.

13:06.720 --> 13:08.720
But just in case
it's not a myth,

13:08.722 --> 13:10.789
I nominate Pedro
to get the bag.

13:10.791 --> 13:14.392
(SCOFFS) Ain't no thing
for a non-vamp.

13:15.361 --> 13:16.694
Ah!

13:17.630 --> 13:20.899
(LAUGHING)

13:20.901 --> 13:22.433
You should see your faces,

13:22.435 --> 13:25.103
all eyes bugging,
mean mugging.

13:25.105 --> 13:27.605
Come on,
y'all got to... Ah!

13:28.641 --> 13:29.507
Ah!

13:29.509 --> 13:31.442
(GASPING) I can't breathe.

13:31.444 --> 13:32.977
Because you're
not breathing.

13:32.979 --> 13:34.345
Oh. (SIGHING)

13:34.347 --> 13:39.684
Don't worry.
Garlic doesn't do anything
to non-vampires.

13:39.686 --> 13:42.854
Oh, and I'm pretty sure
we just proved

13:42.856 --> 13:46.658
garlic seeds
don't do anything
to vampires either.

13:46.660 --> 13:47.892
Look at me.

13:47.894 --> 13:49.527
(HUMMING)

13:49.529 --> 13:53.665
So, maybe garlic
just makes them
dance horribly?

13:53.667 --> 13:55.200
'Kay, we better
put this back

13:55.202 --> 13:57.368
before Quasi finds out
we were in here.

13:57.370 --> 13:58.870
On it!

13:59.238 --> 14:01.072
(SLURPING)

14:02.575 --> 14:04.742
(GRUNTING)

14:06.412 --> 14:09.214
And that's the end of that!

14:18.424 --> 14:19.591
What's that?

14:19.593 --> 14:21.559
(GROWLING)
(SNIFFING)

14:21.561 --> 14:25.230
It couldn't be.
It wouldn't dare.

14:25.232 --> 14:26.731
(SCREAMING)

14:26.733 --> 14:30.668
It is!
You! Pick the sprout!

14:30.769 --> 14:32.103
(GROWLING)

14:32.105 --> 14:34.772
(STAMMERS) Garlic!

14:34.774 --> 14:37.242
(SCREAMING)

14:37.244 --> 14:39.644
(SOBBING)

14:41.747 --> 14:44.649
"Hotel Transylvania
is to remain closed

14:44.651 --> 14:47.051
"while under
garlic decontamination"?

14:47.053 --> 14:50.088
"Closed"? What if we didn't
clean up all those seeds?

14:50.090 --> 14:53.892
If my Dad finds out
I single-handedly
shut down the hotel,

14:53.894 --> 14:55.827
he'll never let me be
in charge.

14:55.829 --> 14:58.196
Man, you'll be lucky
to be assistant to

14:58.198 --> 15:00.398
the Chief Yeti
Tongue Scraper.

15:00.400 --> 15:03.434
Hey, job's already taken.

15:04.336 --> 15:05.803
Well, I, for <i>un,</i>

15:05.805 --> 15:08.473
am relieved
the hotel is closed.

15:08.475 --> 15:10.909
'Cause we all know
what happens to vampires

15:10.911 --> 15:13.244
exposed to garlic, right?

15:13.246 --> 15:14.412
You know, Aunt Lydia,

15:14.414 --> 15:17.048
maybe nothing happens
to vampires?

15:17.050 --> 15:20.051
I've heard the seeds
don't do anything.

15:20.053 --> 15:22.553
Well, of course,
the seeds don't.

15:22.555 --> 15:23.388
(SIGHING)

15:23.390 --> 15:25.523
But once they're
full grown...

15:25.525 --> 15:26.824
(STAMMERS) What?

15:26.826 --> 15:29.160
Horrible, unspeakable things.

15:29.162 --> 15:34.899
Think of the worst thing ever
and multiply it by terrible.

15:34.901 --> 15:35.700
Then you're close.

15:35.702 --> 15:39.404
Dying of hunger
while being scrubbed clean
in a bath?

15:39.406 --> 15:39.771
Even worse.

15:39.773 --> 15:43.274
But it's not as bad
as what's going to happen
to the traitor

15:43.276 --> 15:46.344
who brought garlic
into my hotel.

15:46.346 --> 15:47.045
(GASPING)

15:47.047 --> 15:51.015
How will you ever discover
who did it, huh?

15:51.017 --> 15:53.117
It seems impossible.

15:53.119 --> 15:54.385
(LAUGHING)

15:54.387 --> 15:56.454
The Cerberus
is on the case.

15:56.456 --> 15:58.323
(GROWLING)

15:58.325 --> 15:59.924
It'll sniff out
the garlic source,

15:59.926 --> 16:03.328
which'll have
the culprit's scent.

16:04.463 --> 16:06.397
So, if the hotel's
on lock down,

16:06.399 --> 16:08.466
where are we
supposed to sleep?

16:08.468 --> 16:11.402
(ENGINE STARTING)
Look!

16:14.073 --> 16:16.074
(TIRES SCREECHING)

16:16.076 --> 16:18.309
Looks like they'll be gone
for weeks.

16:18.311 --> 16:22.613
Who's ready for
a Dracula sleepover party?

16:22.615 --> 16:24.682
(GROWLING)

16:27.219 --> 16:28.920
(MEOWING)

16:37.997 --> 16:39.864
Huh?

16:41.333 --> 16:43.434
(SCREAMING)

16:52.478 --> 16:54.946
(SNORING)

16:54.948 --> 16:59.183
(ALL SNORING)

17:10.029 --> 17:11.762
AUNT LYDIA:
Off with their heads!

17:11.765 --> 17:13.564
(CONTINUES SNORING)

17:13.999 --> 17:14.898
(SIGHS)

17:14.901 --> 17:18.935
(GASPS)
(SNORING)

17:19.304 --> 17:21.672
(WHIMPERING)

17:22.641 --> 17:26.377
Wendy? Hey, Wendy?
Wake up.

17:26.378 --> 17:28.746
Fire mouth!
(BOWL CLATTERS)

17:30.549 --> 17:31.783
Morning!

17:31.785 --> 17:32.250
I need help.

17:32.252 --> 17:34.185
I got to sneak back
and grab that bag of seeds

17:34.187 --> 17:36.654
before anyone
finds my prints on it
and I'm sunk.

17:36.656 --> 17:41.259
Imagine, the daughter of
Count Dracula,
caught with garlic.

17:41.960 --> 17:43.961
Now who's with me?

17:43.963 --> 17:48.099
Uh...
We'll guard the tub.
(SNORES)

17:48.101 --> 17:52.637
I think it's time for
a homemade hazmat makeover!

17:55.474 --> 17:56.941
WENDY: Sweet.

17:56.943 --> 17:58.042
Protects against
garlic attack.

17:58.044 --> 18:01.446
(SNIFFS) I can't smell
or hear anything!

18:01.448 --> 18:04.549
Shh!
Mavis did it!

18:04.650 --> 18:07.251
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

18:12.858 --> 18:14.358
I tip, zen I toe.

18:14.360 --> 18:18.262
I tip. I toe. I tip. I toe.
I tip, toe.

18:18.264 --> 18:20.631
(GROWLING)

18:20.633 --> 18:23.000
Tip toe, tip toe,
tip toe, tip toe.

18:23.002 --> 18:25.803
Ze key
is to not wear any socks.

18:28.707 --> 18:30.842
The kitchen? Good idea!

18:30.844 --> 18:34.078
Evidence?
What evidence, Lydia?

18:34.080 --> 18:36.347
(LAUGHING)

18:36.349 --> 18:38.683
Bravo, me.

18:39.985 --> 18:41.219
(GROWLING)

18:41.221 --> 18:44.355
(WHISPERING) How do we
get past the Cerberus?

18:44.357 --> 18:46.657
(LOUDLY) What?
The Cerberus!

18:46.659 --> 18:48.259
(GROWLING)

18:48.261 --> 18:49.894
Run!

18:50.062 --> 18:52.296
(GROWLING)

18:52.798 --> 18:54.899
(GRUNTING)

18:56.201 --> 18:58.703
WENDY: And stay out!

18:58.705 --> 19:03.107
(GRUNTS) That's better.
I can hear now.

19:03.408 --> 19:05.810
(GASPS) It's gone!

19:06.044 --> 19:09.413
Look! Sock-less tippy-toe
footprints!

19:09.715 --> 19:11.816
MAVIS: The incinerator!

19:13.585 --> 19:14.852
Ah! They're still there!

19:14.854 --> 19:18.756
Say, Wendy,
how are you with heat?

19:20.092 --> 19:24.662
Almost, almost.

19:24.664 --> 19:26.964
(GRUNTING) Hey, my gum!

19:28.000 --> 19:31.802
(SCREAMING)

19:31.804 --> 19:33.638
(GRUNTING)
(CLATTERING)

19:33.640 --> 19:36.174
Quasi! What are you
doing here?

19:36.176 --> 19:36.941
Oh, hello.

19:36.943 --> 19:37.975
Uh, visiting the hall
of mirrors,

19:37.977 --> 19:41.746
you know, no crowds for
the decontamination, so...

19:41.748 --> 19:45.283
What are you... <i>Zut alors!</i>
<i>Ze garlic seeds!</i>

19:45.285 --> 19:47.251
(GASPS) Wendy!
You still have them?

19:47.253 --> 19:49.554
(LOUD STOMPING)
Uh-oh! Run!

19:49.556 --> 19:52.123
You're getting good
at saying that.

19:52.125 --> 19:53.124
(GRUNTING)

19:53.126 --> 19:56.460
Your helmet's off!
You're exposed!

19:56.462 --> 19:58.529
(GASPING)

19:58.531 --> 20:02.967
The garlic smell, it's real!
It burns! Make it stop!

20:03.235 --> 20:06.871
(SNIFFS) Can't smell garlic,
thanks, Wendy!

20:06.873 --> 20:09.240
(GROWLING)

20:09.242 --> 20:12.443
(ALL SCREAMING)

20:15.514 --> 20:17.882
(GROWLING)

20:17.884 --> 20:20.451
MAVIS: Wendy, get rid of
the garlic!

20:20.453 --> 20:22.220
Okay, bye-bye, seeds!

20:33.098 --> 20:35.066
Ahem.
I, uh, what?

20:35.068 --> 20:39.437
Oh, wow, where am I?
Sleepwalking, am I right?

20:39.439 --> 20:42.273
(SNIFFING)
Do I smell garlic?

20:42.275 --> 20:42.907
Uh, no.

20:42.909 --> 20:46.611
Besides, I exposed myself.
And nothing happened.

20:46.613 --> 20:49.413
It just burns your nostrils
a bit, big whoop.

20:49.415 --> 20:50.381
I don't believe it.

20:50.383 --> 20:53.417
Well, if I had garlic,
I could prove it.

20:53.419 --> 20:55.886
Oh, you mean like this?

20:56.188 --> 20:57.388
(SCREAMING)

20:57.390 --> 20:59.156
Wendy, why would you
keep that?

20:59.158 --> 21:02.426
Um, hello? It's a keepsake
from our adventure!

21:02.527 --> 21:05.830
Okay, fine, I'll prove it.

21:08.600 --> 21:09.934
(GASPING)

21:12.871 --> 21:16.807
(CHUCKLING) See?
Just a bunch of rubbish.

21:17.476 --> 21:20.344
(SCREAMING)

21:20.346 --> 21:23.514
It's in my mouth!
Is it in my mouth?
It's in my mouth!

21:23.516 --> 21:24.582
(SCREAMING)

21:24.584 --> 21:25.816
UNCLE GENE:
What's happening?

21:25.818 --> 21:28.919
Nothing. (CHUCKLES)
Nothing is happening.

21:28.921 --> 21:30.655
Maybe when it's
second-hand...

21:30.657 --> 21:32.089
(SCREAMING)

21:32.091 --> 21:33.724
(GROWLING)

21:35.661 --> 21:36.861
Ooh!

21:37.596 --> 21:39.797
(SNEEZING)

21:39.965 --> 21:41.599
(BEEPING)

21:41.601 --> 21:43.567
(CREATURES CLAMORING)

21:43.569 --> 21:45.670
(SCREAMING)

21:47.372 --> 21:48.873
(WHIMPERS)

21:50.575 --> 21:52.710
(COUGHING)

21:52.712 --> 21:54.945
Several fiery months later...

21:54.947 --> 21:57.915
When you think about it,
it's almost funny

21:57.917 --> 22:01.652
we all ended up quarantined
to the Cerberus pit.

22:01.654 --> 22:04.722
Yes. It's hilarious.

22:06.058 --> 22:08.459
(MUSIC PLAYING)

22:09.594 --> 22:12.663
(VOCALIZING)
